<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-14T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="900" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8952:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-14T17:00:00-05:00">March 14, 1941—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>28. Colonel Donovan reports from London that the Turkish Government
                                has been notified by Russia that the latter will not join with
                                Germany in any attack on Turkey if Turkey should defend itself
                                against Germany.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>